President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Debo P. Adegbile is nominated for Assistant Attorney General for Civil Rights, Department of Justice. Marc Kastner is nominated for Director of the Office of Science, Department of Energy. Mark E. Lopes is nominated for Member, Board of Directors of the Inter-American Foundation. Vivek Hallegere Murthy is nominated for Surgeon General, Department of Health and Human Services. Franklin Orr is nominated for Under Secretary for Science, Department of Energy. Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Susan L. Graham as a member of the President's Council of Advisors on Science and Technology, and J. Michael McQuade as another member of the President's Council of Advisors on Science and Technology.